Let $\mathbf{a},$ $\mathbf{b},$ and $\mathbf{c}$ be unit vectors, then since $\mathbf{a}+\mathbf{b}+\sqrt{3}\mathbf{c}=\mathbf{0}$ we have $\mathbf{a}+\mathbf{b}=-\sqrt{3}\mathbf{c}$ and after taking the dot product we get \begin{align*}
&(\mathbf{a}+\mathbf{b})\cdot(\mathbf{a}+\mathbf{b})=(-\sqrt{3}\mathbf{c})\cdot(-\sqrt{3}\mathbf{c}) \\
& \quad \mathbf{a}\cdot\mathbf{a}+2\mathbf{a}\cdot\mathbf{b}+\mathbf{b}\cdot\mathbf{b}=(\sqrt{3})^2(\mathbf{c}\cdot\mathbf{c}) \\
& \quad 2+2\mathbf{a}\cdot\mathbf{b}=3 \\
\quad \mathbf{a}\cdot\mathbf{b}&=\frac{1}{2}
\end{align*> <answer> $\boxed{\masked{60}}$>

problem:
In any isosceles triangle $ABC$ with $AB=AC$, the altitude $AD$ bisects the base $BC$ so that $BD=DC$.

Determine the area of $\triangle ABC$.

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(14,0)--(7,24)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
draw((7,24)--(7,0),black+linewidth(1)+dashed);
draw((7,0)--(7,1)--(6,1)--(6,0)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
draw((5.5,-4)--(0,-4),black+linewidth(1));
draw((5.5,-4)--(0,-4),EndArrow);
draw((8.5,-4)--(14,-4),black+linewidth(1));
draw((8.5,-4)--(14,-4),EndArrow);
label("$A$",(7,24),N);
label("$B$",(0,0),SW);
label("$C$",(14,0),SE);
label("$D$",(7,0),S);
label("25",(0,0)--(7,24),NW);
label("25",(7,24)--(14,0),NE);
label("14",(7,-4));
[/asy]

